                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-721">
                        <quote source="#bib721-1">Ṣawma was a monk of the Ch. of E. who, sometime around 1275, set out from Dadu
(also known as Khān Bālīq, i.e. modern Beijing) in his native China with a youngerdisciple, Markos, on a pilgrimage to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/104">Jerusalem</placeName>.</quote>
                    </note>
